VALUES
(44, 5, 37, 18, 20, 5, 9, 'perished; and all, even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed', 'Short-lived triumph of the wicked', 'Both passages emphasize the fleeting nature of the success of the wicked. Acts 5:37 describes Judas of Galilee''s rise and fall, while Job 20:5-9 articulates that the joy of the hypocrite is temporary and leads to destruction.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 37, 19, 7, 14, 15, 'even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed', 'Consequences of Misleading Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of leaders who lead others into destruction. Both passages emphasize the downfall of those who engage in mischief and lead others astray.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 37, 19, 9, 15, 16, 'even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed', 'Judgment and Consequences of Rebellion', 'This connection highlights the theme of judgment against those who lead others astray. Both passages emphasize how the wicked face consequences for their actions, as seen in Judas of Galilee''s downfall and the snaring of the wicked in their own traps.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 37, 40, 26, 52, 52, 'perished; and all, even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed.', 'Perishing for Rebellion', 'This connection highlights the theme of perishing associated with rebellion against authority. Both passages emphasize that those who lead others into conflict or take up arms face dire consequences.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 37, 42, 13, 1, 2, NULL, 'Galileans and Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize Galileans who faced tragic ends. Acts mentions Judas of Galilee, while Luke refers to Galileans whose blood was mingled with sacrifices, suggesting a theme of suffering among Galileans.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 40, 15, 13, 13, 'this counsel or this work be of men', 'Divine Authority in Actions', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority in determining the success of actions. Both passages emphasize that if a work is not established by God, it will ultimately fail.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 23, 8, 9, 10, 'this counsel or this work be of men', 'Counsel and Its Futility', 'This connection highlights the futility of human counsel when it opposes divine will. Both passages emphasize that if a work is of men, it will ultimately come to nought.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 25, 3, 37, 37, 'this counsel or this work be of men', 'Divine Authority in Action', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority over human actions. Both passages emphasize that if something is not commanded by the Lord, it will ultimately fail.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 18, 5, 12, 14, 'this counsel or this work be of men', 'Disappointment of Human Counsel', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of human plans against divine will. Acts 5:38 suggests that if a work is of men, it will fail, while Job 5:12-14 describes how God frustrates the schemes of the crafty.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 19, 33, 10, 11, 'this counsel or this work be of men', 'Counsel of the Lord', 'This connection highlights the theme of counsel and its effectiveness. Both passages emphasize that human plans will ultimately fail if not aligned with God''s will.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 20, 21, 30, 30, 'this counsel or this work', 'Counsel Against the Lord', 'This connection highlights the futility of human counsel when it opposes divine will. Acts 5:38 suggests that if a work is of men, it will fail, while Proverbs 21:30 asserts that no counsel can stand against the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 38, 23, 7, 5, 7, 'this counsel or this work', 'Counsel Against God''s People', 'This connection highlights the theme of counsel that opposes God''s will. Both passages emphasize that if such counsel is not divinely ordained, it will ultimately fail.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 20, 21, 30, 30, 'fight against God', 'Divine Authority and Resistance', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of opposing God. Acts 5:39 warns against fighting against God, while Proverbs 21:30 states there is no counsel against the Lord, highlighting that human wisdom cannot prevail against divine will.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 23, 46, 10, 10, 'ye cannot overthrow it', 'Divine Sovereignty and Counsel', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s ultimate authority and control over events. Both passages emphasize that what is of God cannot be overthrown, affirming His counsel shall stand.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 40, 16, 18, 18, 'ye cannot overthrow it', 'Divine Authority and Resistance', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority, as both passages assert that what is established by God cannot be overthrown. Acts 5:39 emphasizes that opposing God''s work is futile, while Matthew 16:18 declares that the church built on Peter will not be defeated.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 44, 7, 51, 51, 'fight against God', 'Resistance Against God', 'This connection highlights the theme of resisting God. Acts 5:39 warns against fighting against God, while Acts 7:51 directly accuses the people of resisting the Holy Ghost, linking their actions to a historical pattern of defiance.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 44, 11, 17, 17, 'fight against God', 'Divine Authority and Resistance', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of resisting God''s will. Acts 5:39 warns against fighting against God, while Acts 11:17 reflects on the impossibility of withstanding God’s actions.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 46, 1, 25, 25, 'ye cannot overthrow it', 'Divine Wisdom and Strength', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine superiority over human understanding and strength. Both passages emphasize that what may seem foolish or weak from a human perspective is, in fact, part of God''s greater wisdom and power.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 39, 42, 21, 15, 15, 'ye cannot overthrow it', 'Divine Authority and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority in both passages. Acts 5:39 emphasizes that opposing God''s will is futile, while Luke 21:15 promises wisdom that adversaries cannot resist.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 40, 10, 17, 17, NULL, 'Persecution of Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution faced by the apostles. Acts 5:40 describes the apostles being beaten and commanded not to speak, while Matthew 10:17 warns of being delivered to councils and scourged.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 20, 12, 10, 10, 'beaten them', 'Cruelty and Righteousness Contrast', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the treatment of the apostles and the concept of righteousness. Acts 5:40 depicts cruelty through the beating of the apostles, while Proverbs 12:10 emphasizes the compassion expected from a righteous man.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 41, 13, 9, 9, NULL, 'Persecution for Speaking Jesus'' Name', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of being beaten and brought before authorities for proclaiming Jesus. Acts 5:40 describes the apostles being beaten and commanded not to speak in Jesus'' name, while Mark 13:9 warns that followers will be beaten and delivered up to councils for His sake.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 43, 19, 1, 4, 'beaten them', 'Connection of Suffering and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering endured by both Jesus and the apostles. Both passages depict physical punishment, with Jesus being scourged and the apostles being beaten, emphasizing the cost of their commitment to their faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 44, 4, 17, 21, 'not speak in the name of Jesus', 'Threats Against the Apostles', 'Both passages emphasize the threats made against the apostles to stop speaking in the name of Jesus. In Acts 4:17-21, the apostles are commanded not to teach in His name, while in Acts 5:40, they are beaten and similarly commanded. This connection highlights the ongoing opposition faced by the apostles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 44, 5, 28, 28, 'not speak in the name of Jesus', 'Command Against Teaching Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the command not to teach in the name of Jesus. Acts 5:28 highlights the strict command given to the apostles, while Acts 5:40 shows the consequences of their defiance against this command.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 40, 47, 11, 24, 24, 'beaten them', 'Connection of Suffering for Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering endured by the apostles for preaching Jesus. Both passages emphasize the physical punishment received for their faith, illustrating the trials faced by early Christians.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 59, 1, 2, 2, 'rejoicing that they were counted worthy', 'Joy in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing in the face of suffering. Acts 5:41 highlights joy in being shamed for Christ, while James 1:2 encourages joy in various trials.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 60, 4, 13, 16, NULL, 'Rejoicing in Suffering for Christ', 'Both passages emphasize rejoicing in suffering for Christ''s name. They highlight the honor of being reproached for His sake and the resulting joy that comes from sharing in His sufferings.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 42, 6, 22, 22, 'suffer shame for his name', 'Suffering for Christ''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of suffering and reproach for the sake of Jesus. Acts 5:41 reflects the joy of being counted worthy to suffer shame, while Luke 6:22 speaks of the blessing that comes when one is hated and reproached for the Son of Man''s sake.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 50, 1, 29, 29, 'suffer shame for his name', 'Connection of Suffering for Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of suffering for Christ''s sake. Acts 5:41 highlights rejoicing in suffering, while Philippians 1:29 states it is given to suffer for his sake.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 43, 15, 21, 21, 'for his name', 'Suffering for His Name', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering for Jesus'' name. Acts 5:41 highlights rejoicing in suffering, while John 15:21 explains that such suffering occurs because of a lack of understanding of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 40, 5, 10, 12, 'rejoicing that they were counted worthy', 'Persecution and Rejoicing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing in the face of persecution for righteousness'' sake. Acts 5:41 reflects the joy of suffering shame for Jesus'' name, while Matthew 5:10-12 encourages believers to rejoice when persecuted for His sake.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 41, 47, 12, 10, 10, 'suffer shame for his name', 'Suffering for Christ''s Sake', 'Both passages emphasize rejoicing in suffering and weakness for Christ. Acts 5:41 highlights being worthy to suffer shame, while 2 Corinthians 12:10 speaks of taking pleasure in infirmities and persecutions for Christ''s sake.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 44, 2, 46, 46, 'daily in the temple', 'Daily Teaching and Fellowship', 'Both passages emphasize the daily activities of the early believers in teaching and fellowship. Acts 5:42 highlights their continuous teaching of Jesus Christ, while Acts 2:46 describes their daily unity in the temple and breaking bread from house to house.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 42, 21, 37, 37, NULL, 'Teaching in the Temple', 'Both passages emphasize the act of teaching in the temple. Acts 5:42 mentions daily teaching in the temple, while Luke 21:37 describes Jesus teaching there during the day.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 44, 20, 20, 20, NULL, 'Teaching and Preaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of teaching and preaching Jesus Christ in public and private settings. This connection highlights the continuity of the apostles'' mission to spread the message of Jesus in various contexts.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 55, 4, 2, 2, 'teach and preach Jesus Christ', 'Preaching and Teaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of preaching and teaching. Acts 5:42 highlights the continuous effort to teach Jesus Christ, while 2 Timothy 4:2 instructs to preach the word consistently.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 45, 1, 15, 16, 'teach and preach Jesus Christ', 'Preaching the Gospel Connection', 'This connection highlights the commitment to preach the gospel in both passages. Acts 5:42 emphasizes teaching and preaching Jesus Christ, while Romans 1:15 expresses readiness to preach the gospel, underscoring the importance of sharing the message.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 49, 4, 20, 21, 'teach and preach Jesus Christ', 'Teaching and Learning Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of teaching about Jesus. Acts emphasizes the continuous teaching of Jesus Christ, while Ephesians refers to being taught by him, indicating a shared focus on the importance of learning and proclaiming the truth found in Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 5, 42, 10, 6, 22, 22, NULL, 'Teaching and Humility in Service', 'This connection highlights the theme of humility in service. In Acts, the apostles teach daily, showing dedication to their mission, while in 2 Samuel, David expresses a willingness to be base in his own sight for the sake of honor among others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 44, 2, 41, 41, 'the number of the disciples was multiplied', 'Growth of the Early Church', 'Both passages emphasize the increase in disciples. Acts 2:41 notes the addition of three thousand souls, while Acts 6:1 describes the multiplication of disciples, indicating a growing community.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 44, 4, 35, 35, 'daily ministration', 'Distribution and Needs', 'Both passages emphasize the distribution of resources according to need. Acts 6:1 highlights a complaint about neglect in daily support, while Acts 4:35 describes a system of equitable distribution among the community.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 59, 5, 9, 9, 'murmuring of the Grecians', 'Conflict and Community Relations', 'This connection highlights the theme of internal conflict within the community, as seen in Acts with the murmuring of the Grecians and in James with the admonition against grudges. Both passages emphasize the importance of unity and care among believers to avoid division.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 40, 23, 13, 13, 'their widows were neglected', 'Neglect and Hypocrisy in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of neglect in ministry, as seen in the murmuring of the Grecians about their widows being neglected. Both passages emphasize the consequences of failing to care for others, with the Pharisees'' hypocrisy leading to exclusion from the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 50, 3, 5, 5, NULL, 'Cultural Tensions in Early Church', 'This connection highlights the cultural divisions within the early church, as seen in the murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews in Acts. Both passages emphasize the identity of Hebrews, with Philippians focusing on personal heritage and the Acts passage illustrating community dynamics.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 58, 13, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of Love and Care', 'This connection highlights the theme of caring for one another within the community. The murmuring in Acts 6:1 indicates a failure in brotherly love, while Hebrews 13:1 encourages the continuation of that love.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 1, 19, 72, 16, 16, 'widows were neglected in the daily ministration', 'Provision and Flourishing', 'This connection highlights the theme of provision for those in need. In Acts, the neglect of widows contrasts with the flourishing described in Psalms, suggesting a divine promise of care and abundance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 2, 18, 17, 26, 'serve tables', 'Leadership and Delegation', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of delegating responsibilities to avoid overwhelming leaders. In Acts, the apostles recognize they should not leave the word of God, while in Exodus, Moses is advised to appoint able men to share the burden of leadership.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 5, 1, 9, 14, 'serve tables', 'Leadership and Delegation', 'This connection highlights the need for wise leaders to manage burdens. Both passages emphasize the importance of delegating responsibilities to maintain focus on essential tasks.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 55, 2, 4, 4, 'serve tables', 'Focus on Spiritual Duties', 'This connection highlights the importance of prioritizing spiritual responsibilities over worldly concerns. Both passages emphasize the need to remain dedicated to one''s calling without being distracted by other affairs.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 16, 6, 3, 3, 'the word of God', 'Commitment to Important Work', 'This connection highlights the prioritization of significant tasks over lesser duties. Both passages emphasize the necessity of focusing on essential work rather than being distracted by other responsibilities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 4, 11, 11, 13, 'serve tables', 'Burden of Leadership', 'This connection highlights the theme of leadership burdens. Both Moses and the apostles express concern about the demands placed on them, indicating the struggle to balance spiritual responsibilities with practical needs.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 44, 25, 27, 27, 'not reason', 'Reasonableness in Decision Making', 'This connection highlights the theme of reasonableness in decision-making. Both passages emphasize what is deemed ''unreasonable'' in their respective contexts, reflecting the importance of proper prioritization and justification in actions.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 2, 44, 4, 19, 19, 'the word of God', 'Authority of God vs. Service', 'This connection highlights the prioritization of divine authority over earthly responsibilities. Both passages emphasize the necessity of focusing on God''s word rather than being distracted by other duties.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 54, 3, 7, 15, 'honest report', 'Qualifications for Church Leaders', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of having men of ''honest report'' and good character in leadership roles within the church. Acts 6:3 outlines the selection of leaders based on their integrity and wisdom, while 1 Timothy 3:7-15 provides further qualifications for deacons, highlighting the need for a good reputation and moral conduct.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 5, 1, 13, 13, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and Leadership in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the selection of wise individuals for leadership roles. Acts 6:3 calls for men ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom,'' while Deuteronomy 1:13 instructs to ''take you wise men'' for rulership.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 59, 3, 17, 18, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of wisdom in both passages. Acts 6:3 emphasizes selecting men ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom,'' while James 3:17 describes wisdom as ''full of mercy and good fruits,'' linking the qualities of wisdom to righteous actions.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 4, 27, 18, 19, 'full of the Holy Ghost', 'Leadership and Spiritual Qualification', 'Both passages emphasize the selection of leaders who are filled with the Spirit. Acts 6:3 mentions men ''full of the Holy Ghost,'' while Numbers 27:18 refers to Joshua as ''a man in whom is the spirit.'' This connection highlights the importance of spiritual qualifications in leadership roles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 54, 5, 10, 10, 'honest report', 'Qualifications for Service', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being ''well reported of'' and having a good reputation in the community. Acts 6:3 focuses on selecting men of honest report, while 1 Timothy 5:10 highlights good works as a measure of a woman''s reputation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 44, 13, 2, 3, 'full of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Holy Spirit and Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Ghost in guiding leadership decisions within the early church. In Acts 6:3, the selection of leaders is based on being ''full of the Holy Ghost,'' while Acts 13:2-3 shows the Holy Ghost directing the calling of Barnabas and Saul.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 3, 1, 41, 38, 39, 'full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom', 'Wisdom and the Spirit of God', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on being ''full of the Holy Ghost and wisdom'' in Acts, paralleling Pharaoh''s recognition of Joseph as ''discreet and wise'' in Genesis. Both passages underscore the importance of divine wisdom and the Spirit of God in leadership roles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 44, 1, 14, 14, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer within the early church community. Acts 6:4 highlights the commitment to prayer alongside ministry, while Acts 1:14 shows the collective devotion to prayer among the believers.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 54, 4, 13, 16, 'ministry of the word', 'Ministry and Doctrine Emphasis', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of ministry and doctrine. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer and the ministry of the word, while 1 Timothy 4:13-16 encourages attention to reading, exhortation, and doctrine.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 50, 1, 9, 11, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and spiritual growth. Acts 6:4 highlights prayer and ministry, while Philippians 1:9-11 focuses on love and righteousness, suggesting a link between prayerful devotion and the fruits of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 44, 2, 42, 42, 'to prayer', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in the early church. Acts 6:4 highlights the commitment to prayer and ministry, while Acts 2:42 mentions prayers as a key practice of the believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 55, 4, 2, 2, 'ministry of the word', 'Connection of Ministry and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the ministry of the word. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer and the ministry, while 2 Timothy 4:2 focuses on preaching the word with diligence.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 45, 1, 9, 9, 'prayer, and to the ministry of the word', 'Prayer and Ministry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer in the context of ministry. Acts 6:4 highlights a commitment to prayer and the ministry of the word, while Romans 1:9 reflects a personal dedication to prayer in service to the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 4, 49, 3, 14, 21, 'prayer', 'Prayer and Spiritual Strength', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of prayer and spiritual empowerment. Acts 6:4 highlights dedication to prayer, while Ephesians 3:16 speaks of being strengthened by the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 44, 11, 24, 24, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Faith and the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize being ''full of the Holy Ghost and of faith.'' This connection highlights the importance of these qualities in the early church and their role in attracting others to the faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 44, 21, 8, 8, 'Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor', 'Connection of Philip the Evangelist', 'Both passages emphasize Philip''s role in the early church. In Acts 6:5, he is chosen as one of the seven, and in Acts 21:8, he is identified as Philip the evangelist, linking his ministry across the narrative.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 20, 15, 23, 23, NULL, 'Joy in Wise Choices', 'This connection highlights the joy that comes from making wise decisions, as seen in Acts 6:5 where the community chooses Stephen and others, reflecting the good outcome of their choice. Proverbs 15:23 emphasizes the joy of timely words, suggesting that both passages celebrate the positive results of thoughtful actions and decisions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 1, 41, 37, 37, 'the saying pleased the whole multitude', 'Agreement Among Leaders', 'This connection highlights the approval of a decision by a group. Both passages emphasize the positive reception of choices made by leaders and their followers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 20, 15, 1, 1, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Response and Leadership', 'This connection highlights the importance of a calm and measured response in leadership, as seen in Stephen''s selection for his faith and character. Proverbs emphasizes that a soft answer can diffuse anger, paralleling the qualities needed in those chosen to lead.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 33, 3, 8, 8, 'full of faith and of the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Spiritual Empowerment', 'Both passages emphasize being ''full of'' the Spirit, highlighting the importance of divine empowerment for ministry and proclamation. Stephen is described as ''full of faith and of the Holy Ghost,'' while Micah speaks of being ''full of power by the spirit of the Lord.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 5, 40, 23, 15, 15, 'a proselyte of Antioch', 'Connection of Proselytes in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of proselytes, highlighting the contrasting views on their significance. Acts 6:5 mentions Nicolas, a proselyte, while Matthew 23:15 critiques the Pharisees'' approach to making proselytes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 6, 6, 4, 8, 10, 10, 'laid their hands on them', 'Connection of Laying on Hands', 'This connection highlights the act of laying hands as a means of consecration and commissioning. Both passages emphasize the communal involvement in setting apart individuals for service.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
